From @realmoney Facebook's Sharp Share Price Advance May Now Stall When I purchased Facebook (and placed it on my Best Ideas List at $137 in late November, 2018) it -along with Goldman Sachs - were my favorite large cap longs.

The stocks were substantially out of favor and hated by the sell- and buy- side. Since then, conditions have changed. Facebook's shares have steadily risen (by over $35/share) to $173 since then and I have recently reduced this long holding to tag ends. realmoney.thestreet.com/doug…

The principal reasons for my sale were: * A reduced upside reward vs. downside risk. (We were paid off for our contrarian buy last year) * It has become increasingly clear that Facebook faces continued legal scrutiny and that last year's setbacks may not yet be behind the

company. (See this NY Times column on the most recent charge with regard to data deals nytimes.com/2019/03/13/techn…) Nevertheless, as I mentioned yesterday I would be a buyer of FB on weakness - but only if it fell to $157.50 or below. I prefer $GOOGL and $AMZN to Facebook in FANG .
